    "Social media significantly alters behavioral patterns by encouraging compulsive checking habits and reducing face-to-face interaction time, which disrupts traditional sleep schedules and study routines.",
    "The social fabric of adolescent communities is redefined through algorithmic curation, where echo chambers can isolate groups and limit exposure to diverse perspectives, thereby narrowing the scope of social learning.",
    "Digital engagement metrics often replace genuine connection, leading to a performative culture where the act of posting and receiving likes becomes a primary driver of daily motivation and identity construction."
